---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base
  title="What Is TOG Rating? A Complete Guide for Baby Sleeping Bags"
  description="TOG stands for Thermal Overall Grade — the standard measure of warmth in baby sleeping bags. Learn what TOG ratings mean and how to choose the right one."
>
  <Nav />

  <article class="article">
    <div class="article-hero">
      <div class="container article-hero-inner">
        <div class="label">Buyer's Guide</div>
        <h1>What Is TOG Rating? A Complete Guide for Baby Sleeping Bags</h1>
        <div class="article-meta">
          <span>Published: March 1, 2025</span>
          <span>·</span>
          <span>By Lianchuang Textile</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container article-body">
      <div class="article-content">

        <p class="lead">
          If you're sourcing or designing baby sleeping bags for your brand, TOG rating is the single most important product specification you need to understand. This guide explains what TOG means, how the scale works, and how to choose the right rating for your market.
        </p>

        <h2>What Does TOG Stand For?</h2>
        <p>TOG stands for <strong>Thermal Overall Grade</strong> — a unit of measurement used to indicate the thermal insulation of a fabric or product. The higher the TOG, the warmer the product.</p>
        <p>In the context of baby sleeping bags, TOG rating tells parents (and buyers) exactly how warm a sleep bag is, so they can match it to the room temperature their baby sleeps in.</p>

        <h2>The TOG Scale Explained</h2>
        <div class="tog-table">
          <div class="tog-row tog-row-header">
            <span>TOG Rating</span><span>Season</span><span>Room Temperature</span><span>Description</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tog-row">
            <span class="tog-val">0.5</span><span>Summer</span><span>24–27°C</span><span>Lightweight, very breathable</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tog-row">
            <span class="tog-val">1.0</span><span>Spring / Autumn</span><span>20–24°C</span><span>Versatile, year-round bestseller</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tog-row">
            <span class="tog-val">2.5</span><span>Autumn / Winter</span><span>16–20°C</span><span>Warm and cozy</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tog-row">
            <span class="tog-val">3.5</span><span>Winter</span><span>12–16°C</span><span>Maximum warmth for cold climates</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2>Why TOG Rating Matters for Your Brand</h2>
        <p>For brands and retailers, TOG rating is not just a product specification — it's a selling point and a safety communication tool. European markets in particular expect TOG ratings to be clearly labeled on all baby sleeping bags.</p>
        <p>Getting the TOG right for your target market is critical. A brand selling into Scandinavian markets will need a heavier TOG range than one targeting Australian or Southeast Asian customers.</p>

        <h2>How We Manufacture to TOG Specification</h2>
        <p>At Lianchuang Textile, each TOG rating is achieved through a combination of fabric weight, knit structure, and fill material. Our production team works with your specification to hit the target TOG consistently across bulk production.</p>
        <p>We manufacture TOG 0.5, 1.0, 2.5, and 3.5 sleeping bags in organic cotton, bamboo blend, and merino wool — all available for OEM and ODM customization.</p>

        <div class="article-cta">
          <h3>Ready to Source Baby Sleeping Bags?</h3>
          <p>We manufacture custom TOG-rated sleeping bags for brands worldwide. GOTS certified, BSCI audited, low MOQ from 300 pcs.</p>
          <a href="/#contact" class="btn btn-primary">Request a Sample →</a>
        </div>

      </div>

      <aside class="article-sidebar">
        <div class="sidebar-card card">
          <h4>Our TOG Range</h4>
          <div class="sidebar-links">
            <a href="/products/tog-05">☀️ TOG 0.5 Summer Bag</a>
            <a href="/products/tog-10">🌤️ TOG 1.0 All-Season</a>
            <a href="/products/tog-25">🍂 TOG 2.5 Winter Bag</a>
            <a href="/products/tog-35">❄️ TOG 3.5 Cold Climate</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sidebar-card card">
          <h4>Get a Quote</h4>
          <p>Custom baby sleeping bags from 300 pcs. GOTS & BSCI certified.</p>
          <a href="/#contact" class="btn btn-primary" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;margin-top:1rem;">Contact Us</a>
        </div>

        <div class="sidebar-card card">
          <h4>Related Articles</h4>
          <div class="sidebar-links">
            <a href="/blog/gots-certified-baby-products">Why GOTS Certification Matters</a>
            <a href="/blog/organic-cotton-vs-bamboo-vs-merino">Cotton vs Bamboo vs Merino</a>
            <a href="/blog/en-16781-safety-standard">EN 16781 Safety Standard</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </article>

  <Footer />
</Base>

<style>
.article-hero {
  padding: 130px 0 60px;
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--cream), var(--cream-dark));
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}
.article-hero h1 {
  font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3vw, 2.8rem);
  color: var(--warm); margin-bottom: 1rem; max-width: 700px;
}
.article-meta {
  display: flex; gap: 0.6rem;
  font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--text-light);
}
.article-body {
  display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 320px;
  gap: 4rem; padding: 4rem 5%; align-items: start;
}
.article-content { max-width: 720px; }
.lead {
  font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--text-light);
  line-height: 1.85; font-weight: 300; margin-bottom: 2rem;
  border-left: 3px solid var(--blush); padding-left: 1.2rem;
}
.article-content h2 {
  font-size: 1.5rem; color: var(--warm);
  margin: 2rem 0 0.8rem;
}
.article-content p {
  font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-light);
  line-height: 1.85; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-weight: 300;
}
.tog-table {
  border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 16px;
  overflow: hidden; margin: 1.5rem 0;
}
.tog-row {
  display: grid; grid-template-columns: 0.6fr 1fr 1fr 1.5fr;
  padding: 0.9rem 1.2rem; gap: 1rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  font-size: 0.85rem; align-items: center;
}
.tog-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
.tog-row-header {
  background: var(--warm); color: white;
  font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.06em;
}
.tog-row:nth-child(even):not(.tog-row-header) { background: var(--cream); }
.tog-val { font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--blush); }
.article-cta {
  background: var(--cream-dark); border-radius: 20px;
  padding: 2rem; margin-top: 3rem; border: 1px solid var(--border);
}
.article-cta h3 {
  font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--warm); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}
.article-cta p { font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--text-light); margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.6; }

/* Sidebar */
.article-sidebar { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.2rem; position: sticky; top: 90px; }
.sidebar-card h4 {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 1rem; color: var(--warm); margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
  padding-bottom: 0.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}
.sidebar-card p { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--text-light); line-height: 1.6; }
.sidebar-links { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; }
.sidebar-links a {
  font-size: 0.83rem; color: var(--text-light);
  padding: 0.4rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  transition: color 0.2s;
}
.sidebar-links a:hover { color: var(--blush); }

@media (max-width: 900px) {
  .article-body { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .article-sidebar { position: static; }
}
</style>
